            li
                p.fact The amount of hate crimes related to gender-identity increased by 20% in 2019.
            li
                p.fact 22% of transgender people who have interacted with police reported experiencing police harassment.
            li
                p.fact With discrimination in jobs, education and services, poverty has long been a queer issue. The trans community are twice as likely to be unemployed compared to cisgender individuals.
            li
                p.fact 90% of the trans community report having experienced some kind of harassment, mistreatment and discrimination in the workplace. One survey found that only 30% of homeless shelters were open to housing transgender women. As a result, LGBTQ-identified people (namely trans people) often rely on sex work as a means of survival.
